<blockquote>   <p>My data is being displayed from the controller. "ng-repeat" works fine when displaying the data, but "ng-submit" is not adding new data to the model using the following code: </p>      <p>pages.js.coffee</p> </blockquote>  <pre><code>  @PagesController = ($scope) -&gt;    $scope.entries = [      {name:"Larry"}      {name:"Curly"}      {name:"Mo"}      {name:"Ralph"}     ]      $scope.addEntry = -&gt;      $scope.entries.push($scope.newEntry)      $scope.newEntry = {} </code></pre>  <blockquote>   <p>index.html.erb</p> </blockquote>  <pre><code>  &lt;div ng-controller="PagesController"&gt;       &lt;h1&gt;Angular &amp; Rails&lt;/h1&gt;      &lt;form ng-submit="addEntry"&gt;       &lt;input type="text" ng-model="newEntry.name"&gt;       &lt;input type="submit" value="Add"&gt;     &lt;/form&gt;      &lt;ul&gt;       &lt;li ng-repeat="entry in entries"&gt;         {{entry.name}}       &lt;/li&gt;     &lt;/ul&gt;     &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>